  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p>\n<p>Rinse the <strong>brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p>\n<p>Once cooked, drain and return it to the pot</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1738.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1738.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1738.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1738.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1738.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, trim the green stalks off the <strong>aubergine<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and cut, lengthways into wedges</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>harissa</strong> and<strong> honey</strong> to a large bowl and season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> – this is your <strong>marinade</strong></p>\n<p>Add the <strong>aubergine wedges</strong> to the <strong>marinade</strong> and coat well</p>\n<p>Transfer the coated <strong>aubergine wedges</strong> to a baking tray, drizzle them with <strong>olive oil</strong> and put the tray in the oven for 25 min or until browned and softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1738.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1738.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1738.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1738.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1738.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>green beans</strong> roughly</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>beans</strong> to a pot of <strong>cold water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 5-6 min or until cooked with a slight bite </p>\n<p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pot and set aside</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1738.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
